The paper is focused on the formal specification and verification of autonomous robotic systems, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the challenges arising from software architectures, which suggests that software engineering (cs.SE) is another relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the cyber-physical attributes of robotic systems, which is a key aspect of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of formal methods for verification is also a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL).
